news.title: China Evergrande Group to hire more advisers to help deal with debt
news.para: Evergrande is the world's most-indebted property company with more than $300 billion in liabilities, including nearly $20 billion of international bonds all deemed to be in default after a run of missed payments late last year.

news.title: Birla Corporation inaugurates Rs 2,744-crore Mukutban cement plant
news.para: The greenfield project of RCCPL Private Ltd, a wholly owned subsidiary of the cement maker, takes the group's total installed capacity to 20 million tonne per annum.

news.title: Gurugram: About 1,000 illegal jhuggis near Golf Gourse Road razed
news.para: A day after sealing 10 commercial establishments running from residential plots in the colony, the department targetted unauthorised jhuggis constructed despite ban on construction in the colony.

news.title: Soon, drone survey of properties in 31 districts of Karnataka
news.para: Revenue minister R Ashoka on Thursday told reporters the move is in line with the Centre's flagship Digital India programme. He said the department has already begun a pilot project in five districts, including Ramanagara, under the central government scheme.

news.title: Bengaluru metro's airport line 49 properties away
news.para: ​While the BMRCL has been able to acquire 224 properties (175 private and 49 government), it is yet to acquire 49 (38 private and 11 government) properties. Sources said that once these properties are acquired, then the entire project will be fast tracked.

news.title: Kolkata: Get jabbed twice, claim property tax discount
news.para: To encourage people to take both the doses of Covid vaccine, South Dum Dum Municipality is planning to allow a 25% relaxation on unpaid property tax if all the family members of the household furnish their vaccination certificate.

news.title: Aparna Constructions to invest Rs 2,550 crore in Puppalaguda project
news.para: The project will be built on 37 acres and will comprise of 3,664 apartments spread across 33 floors and 14 blocks. It will comprise of 1 BHK, 2 BHK and 3 BHK apartments ranging from 1,020 sq. ft to 2,257 sq. ft.

news.title: PVC pipe makers set for 35% revenue growth this fiscal: Crisil
news.para: This fiscal, operating profitability is expected to moderate to 16-17% from the peak of last fiscal, mainly due to higher PVC resin prices, which are being passed on with a lag, and higher freight costs.

news.title: Thane may get property tax waiver for homes measuring up to 500 sq ft
news.para: Speaking to reporters after the weekly cabinet meeting here, Eknath Shinde said a proposal to waive property tax on houses with an area of up to 500 sq ft in Thane city was discussed in the meet.

news.title: Move to cancel title deeds in Munnar kicks up a row
news.para: The controversial title deeds known as ‘Raveendran pattayams’ were allegedly issued illegally by M I Raveendran, the then additional tahsildar in 1999.

news.title: Allotment of plots begins at MIDC's Ajang estate
news.para: This new estate is spread over 345 hectare and the MIDC has allotted plots to over 200 MSMEs in food and textile sectors that are expected to fetch investment amounting to Rs 1,000 crore during the next two-three years and will provide employments to over 4,000 people.

news.title: Won't regularise constructions within 300 metre of Sonar Fort: Jaisalmer civic body
news.para: The division bench of Justice Sandeep Mehta and Justice Sameer Jain, in the previous hearing of a PIL moved by a resident Sunil Paliwal in December, extended stay on any proceedings pertaining to issuance of pattas in the protected, prohibited and regulated areas inside and around the fort.

news.title: Sand set to get cheaper in Maharashtra under new mining policy
news.para: In a press release, the government said the new policy will ensure that river and creek sand and gravel is available at a more reasonable rate and the license for sand mining will be valid for five years after the successful auctioneer has obtained a letter of intent along with environmental permits.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance's net profit down 19% at Rs 188 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income during October-December period of 2021-22 stood at Rs 1,495.61 crore, down by 26.8 per cent from Rs 1,896.35 crore in same quarter of 2020-21, PNB Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Why are we charged for infrastructure: Gurugram residents to DHBVN
news.para: However, this decision of Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (DHBVN) to recover the ‘development charges’ from new consumers or existing ones seeking load enhancement has drawn flak from the residents.
